            <tr>
				<td align="left">

					 <p></p><h1>Overview</h1><p></p>

				</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td> 
				<!--Ìí¼Ó¼ò½é-------------------------------------------------------------------------->
				<p>
				</p><div id="overview"><b>BitMapper</b> is an efficient reads mappers for short reads of equal length. It is designed to output all mapping locations for each reads. It is useful for applications, such as ChIP-seq experiments, CNVs (copy number varia-tion) calling and detecting structural variants. BitMapper is freely available at <a href="http://home.ustc.edu.cn/~chhy/BitMapper.html">BitMapper</a>.
<br>

<br><b>BitMapper2</b> is a GPU-accelerated all-mapper that exploits the parallel processing capability of GPUs to improve the speed. Besides, the peak memory of BitMapper2 is low enough to map reads onto human genomes on a standard PC. BitMapper2 is freely available at <a href="http://home.ustc.edu.cn/~chhy/BitMapper2.html">BitMapper2</a>
</div><p></p>
				<!------------------------------------------------------------------------------------>
				</td>
			</tr>
